Product hierarchy refers to the categorization of products based on their characteristics, features, or functions; 
Categories can include product types like electronics, clothing, etc.; 
Supplier information might be used to track inventory, manage orders, and negotiate prices;
Warehouse stock and product variations are used to manage inventory levels;
Order items are used to calculate total sales and average sale prices;
User permissions determine the level of access users have to product information and other data;
Products with no category ID are considered top-level products, and products belonging to these are considered sub-products or variations.

- "Electronics" refers to the category of products that include electronic devices and gadgets; 
- "still in stock" means that the product has a total quantity greater than 0; 
- "within the past month" refers to the 30-day time frame used in the query.
